(210, 1, '2021-10-04 08:08:33', '2021-10-04 08:08:33', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the mid-1990s when the collection of material for the Tocumwal Archive began there were still a number of long term residents in the O\'Connor Tocumwal houses, some of whom were the original tenants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {"className":"is-style-wide"} -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator is-style-wide"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">I don’t ever want to go</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we came there wasn’t a thing out this way<br>There was a big black stump over the street there<br>Right in the middle of the two way street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/i-dont-ever-want-to-go/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">The story of Studio Nundah – Macarthur Avenue</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pottery studio at the back of the Macarthur Avenue house was built by my father with the aid of Jack Ketley, the head of the Electrical Trades, and a number of other people involved in the trade areas of the Tech.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/the-story-of-studio-nundah-macarthur-avenue/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">My life with the ponies and horses</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We arrived in Australia in 1966 and bought this house in Quinn Street, O’Connor. The house, a Tocumwal type, had a huge back yard. There were all types of fruit trees, pencil pines and nut trees growing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/my-life-with-the-ponies-and-horses/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Long term residents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'long-term-residents', '', '', '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '', 11, 'http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/?page_id=210', 0, 'page', '', 0),
