(212, 1, '2021-10-04 08:10:40', '2021-10-04 08:10:40', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we came there wasn\'t a thing out this way<br>There was a big black stump over the street there<br>Right in the middle of the two way street<br>And the children used to play in it and get covered with charcoal.<br>The best baby sitter I ever had was an old magpie that used to sit up on a big dead stump on the corner of<br>Miller and Macarthur<br>Every time the children got to the corner it used to swoop down on them<br>It knew!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We used to push the pram with the kids in to do the shopping at Civic - and bring it home in the pram<br>Usually the day after you got paid<br>It was the only shopping centre</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr Cosier was at the corner store<br>After he sold up and went away they built the whole front right along<br>There was a little clothing shop - Macdonald\'s - past the chemist shop - where (Marinetti\'s) is now<br>We used to use it quite a lot</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My girls and George\'s (George Lewis) girls all went to school together<br>We used to go down to Turner School for Sunday School<br>And they all went from there to St Phillips - at the youth centre there<br>Both my girls were married at St Phillips<br>And my husband was buried from there.<br>I remember when we put the first stone in for the Church</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I still do morning teas once a month.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We knew all our neighbours<br>But they\'re all changed now<br>The LeGrand\'s had the art gallery<br>The Macmillans were on the corner of Way Street<br>The Crosses were in Miller Street for years<br>Neighbours didn\'t get together for functions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But we did things like swapping vegetables - and we still do<br>George and I are often swapping things</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And George is very handy if you want anything fixed</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We had a fire in the lounge room<br>And a wood stove in the kitchen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That was all the heating we had.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The front part\'s the same as it always was<br>I had the new and bigger windows put in because they were push out windowns and were always breaking<br>And I got a hot water service in the bathroom<br>When we moved in we had a chip heater - that was alright when we had the wood</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When my husband was alive he wouldn\'t buy the house<br>But after he died they put the rents up - about $100 per fortnight</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So I bought it and put the extra 100 into the house instead of the rent<br>It\'s all paid for now</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now I have three girls living with me - two have been here for two years<br>Before that I had other students - most of them were from the country<br>It\'s company for me in the house<br>I had one come and visit me a little while ago - she\'d lived here for about nine years<br>Any of them, if they\'re around they always come and see me</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We were the third people in this house<br>I\'ve been here about 45 years<br>And I don\'t ever want to go<br>When I first saw the house I loved it<br>A real home place<br>My granddaughter says to me now<br>\'Don\'t ever sell it Gran or we\'ll have nowhere to call home\'</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I like it here because it\'s handy to everything<br>And I\'ve been here - you get to know your way around places<br>I don\'t think I\'d like to move anywhere else</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Dot Mayo, Macarthur Avenue, 1950-1998 (contributed 1996)</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'I don\'t ever want to go', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'i-dont-ever-want-to-go', '', '', '2021-10-04 08:10:40', '2021-10-04 08:10:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/?p=212', 0, 'post', '', 0),
