(230, 1, '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the mid-1990s when the collection of material for the Tocumwal Archive began there were still a number of long term residents in the O\'Connor Tocumwal houses, some of whom were the original tenants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {"className":"is-style-wide"} -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator is-style-wide"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">I don’t ever want to go</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we came there wasn’t a thing out this way<br>There was a big black stump over the street there<br>Right in the middle of the two way street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/i-dont-ever-want-to-go/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">The story of Studio Nundah – Macarthur Avenue</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pottery studio at the back of the Macarthur Avenue house was built by my father with the aid of Jack Ketley, the head of the Electrical Trades, and a number of other people involved in the trade areas of the Tech.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/the-story-of-studio-nundah-macarthur-avenue/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">My life with the ponies and horses</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We arrived in Australia in 1966 and bought this house in Quinn Street, O’Connor. The house, a Tocumwal type, had a huge back yard. There were all types of fruit trees, pencil pines and nut trees growing. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/my-life-with-the-ponies-and-horses/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Long term residents', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '2021-10-04 13:35:13', '', 210, 'http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/?p=230', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(231, 1, '2021-10-04 13:41:34', '2021-10-04 13:41:34', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After the Second World War, the development of Canberra as the national capital was revitalised. The final move of central Commonwealth administration from Melbourne to Canberra involved thousands of people and a huge building program that included the creation of new suburbs as well as offices, schools and all the general city infrastructure. In its quest to meet the growing housing needs of Canberra at a time of extreme shortage of building materials the National Capital Planning and Development Committee was interested in available prefabricated houses. The transportation of a number of the Tocumwal houses and their installation in Ainslie and O’Connor was arranged. In Ainslie they were located in various streets amongst other types of housing, but in O’Connor they were established in a specific location that is now the O’Connor Tocumwal heritage precinct. Jim Perry was the builder who won the contract to install the houses in O’Connor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {"className":"is-style-wide"} -->\n<hr class="wp-block-separator is-style-wide"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">On the road</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I lived near the Murray Valley Highway. I remember seeing houses in sections going along the highway on big trucks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/on-the-road/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">Unloading in O’Connor</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alby and Dot Day moved into Hart Street in 1949. At this time the Tocumwal houses were still being put up in the O’Connor area.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/unloading-in-oconnor/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">‘Who ever thought we’d get a Tocumwal house!’</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>John Barty was employed as a carpenter on the construction of houses at the Tocumwal air force base. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/who-ever-thought-wed-get-a-tocumwal-house/">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"fontSize":"normal"} -->\n<h2 class="has-normal-font-size">Owen Taverner – bricklayer – contract for 100 Tocumwal cottages in O’Connor</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Owen Taverner and his partners Billy Moore and Billy Goggin had the contract with Jim Perry to build the footings and chimneys.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"fontSize":"small"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-button has-custom-font-size has-small-font-size"><a class="wp-block-button__link">View</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->', 'From Tocumwal to Canberra', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '163-autosave-v1', '', '', '2021-10-04 13:41:34', '2021-10-04 13:41:34', '', 163, 'http://localhost:8888/WP/example/Wordpress/?p=231', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
